## 3\. Hospitality & Estates — Administrative Layer (Admin Only)
* * *
## 3.1 HR Administration
**Route:** `/hospitality-estates/admin/hr`
**Who uses it:** HR executives, senior operations managers
### HR Executive Dashboard
**Purpose:** Control staffing quality, availability, compliance and service excellence across all properties.
**What the admin sees**
*   Staff count by property, estate and event
*   Staff-to-guest ratios (real-time + seasonal)
*   Peak-period staffing gaps
*   Department performance trends (front desk, concierge, security, housekeeping, events)
**What the admin controls**
*   Cross-property staff transfers and redeployment
*   Minimum service staffing thresholds per property type
*   Mandatory luxury service training rules
*   Uniform, grooming, and brand standards enforcement
* * *
### Luxury Staff Management
**Route:** `/hospitality-estates/admin/hr/staff-management`
**Admin capabilities**
*   Assign concierge and butler tiers (standard, VIP, ultra-luxury)
*   Allocate staff across multiple properties and estates
*   Track guest satisfaction scores per staff member
**Why this matters**
*   Direct link between service quality and revenue
*   Identifies top performers and service risks early
* * *
### Event Staff Coordination
**Route:** `/hospitality-estates/admin/hr/event-staff`
**Admin capabilities**
*   Deploy staff per event type (wedding, corporate, private)
*   Assign specialized training requirements
*   Approve temporary or contract staff
*   Monitor staff-to-guest ratios for events
**Admin control**
*   Maximum event workload per staff member
*   Mandatory certifications before event assignment
* * *
### Estate Staff & Security Management
**Route:** `/hospitality-estates/admin/hr/estate-management`
**Admin capabilities**
*   Assign estate-specific staff roles
*   Manage maintenance, grounds, and technical teams
*   Control security personnel rotation
*   Plan seasonal staffing increases
**System reminders**
*   Certification expiry
*   Performance review cycles
*   Training renewals
* * *
## 3.2 Finance Administration
**Route:** `/hospitality-estates/admin/finance`
**Who uses it:** Finance directors, property owners, executives
### Finance Executive Dashboard
**Purpose:** Full financial visibility and control across properties, estates, and events.
**What the admin sees**
*   Revenue per property, estate, and event
*   Occupancy, ADR, RevPAR trends
*   Event contribution to total revenue
*   Visitor-paid revenue (consultations, events, access)
**What the admin controls**
*   Pricing rules and revenue targets
*   Platform fees on visitor payments
*   Event commission structures
* * *
### Multi-Property Revenue Management
**Route:** `/hospitality-estates/admin/finance/revenue`
**Admin capabilities**
